msgid "The inverse of `hfft`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.hfft:70
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.hfft:71
msgid ""
"`hfft`/`ihfft` are a pair analogous to `rfft`/`irfft`, but for the opposite "
"case: here the signal has Hermitian symmetry in the time domain and is real "
"in the frequency domain. So here it's `hfft` for which you must supply the "
"length of the result if it is to be odd."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.hfft:76
msgid "even: ``ihfft(hfft(a, 2*len(a) - 2)) == a``, within roundoff error,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.hfft:77
msgid "odd: ``ihfft(hfft(a, 2*len(a) - 1)) == a``, within roundoff error."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.13/site-packages/numpy/fft/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.fft.hfft:79
msgid ""
"The correct interpretation of the hermitian input depends on the length of "
"the original data, as given by `n`. This is because each input shape could "
"correspond to either an odd or even length signal. By default, `hfft` "
"assumes an even output length which puts the last entry at the Nyquist "
"frequency; aliasing with its symmetric counterpart. By Hermitian symmetry, "
"the value is thus treated as purely real. To avoid losing information, the "
"shape of the full signal **must** be given."
msgstr ""

